09/03/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Defence Minister Jovan Manasievski is scheduled to visit NATO HQ in Brussels on Wednesday (9 March) and meet with Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer. 
The talks are expected to focus on defence reforms in the country as well as Macedonia's further participation in NATO peacekeeping missions abroad. 
Manasievski will also meet with his Belgian counterpart, Andre Flahaut, and sign a bilateral agreement on co-operation in the defence sector. 
(Makfax - 09/03/05; NATO Web site - 08/03/05)
